Linda was born on May $6$\textsuperscript{th}. Her brother was born $9$ days earlier than her. When her brother was born? (adapted from $$2008$$ Math kangaroo Problems, Level $$1-2$$, Question \#$$4$$) 

Options:
A. April $27$\textsuperscript{th} 
B. May $15$\textsuperscript{th} 
C. April $28$\textsuperscript{th} 
D. April $26$\textsuperscript{th} 
E. May $16$\textsuperscript{th}

\textbf{\hspace{0pt}If a business owner has a \textsuperscript{$}100,000 accounting profit and could have made exactly $60,000 in his next best business opportunity, he has earned} 

Options:
A. \textbf{$160,000 in economic profits.} 
B. \textbf{$100,000 in economic profits.} 
C. \textbf{$40,000 in economic profits.} 
D. \textbf{neither an economic profit or loss.} 
E. \textbf{none of the above.}

\textbf{Daniel is learning that five pennies spread out on his desk are the same number of coins as five pennies in a pile. According to Piaget, how old is Daniel likely to be?} 

Options:
A. 1~\textbf{year} 
B. 2~\textbf{years} 
C. \textbf{4 years} 
D. \textbf{8 years} 
E. \textbf{13 years}

